<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: REPORTS OF TOXIC LEAKS FORCE 2 EVACUATIONS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Two small commercial areas of the northeast San Fernando Valley were evacuated 
briefly Tuesday when hazardous materials leaks were reported, the Los Angeles 
Fire Department said. 
</P>
<P>
A small vat containing trichloroethane overheated and caught fire about 1 p.m. 
at Anthony Manufacturing in the 12300 block of Montero Avenue in Pacoima, 
Firefighter Pat Marek said. 
</P>
<P>
Marek said nearby businesses were evacuated as a precaution for about an hour. 
</P>
<P>
Earlier in the day, a hazardous-materials team was sent to an out of business 
metal-plating company in Sun Valley where chemicals were reported to be leaking 
from a steel drum. Marek said the report came from workers cleaning up 
All-American Plating, in the 7100 block of Vineland Avenue. 
</P>
<P>
A small area of nearby businesses was evacuated after the leak was reported at 
10:35 a.m., but no indication of a leak was found, Marek said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
