<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: SAN DIEGO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A prisoner attacked a bailiff in the downtown courthouse Tuesday, and the 
bailiff was taken to a hospital for treatment. 
</P>
<P>
County Marshal Michael Sgobba) said Ricky Spells allegedly hit the bailiff with 
his fists in an inmate holding tank as Spells' handcuffs were being removed. 
</P>
<P>
"It was an assault in the holding area. He was being returned from court. The 
deputy was unhandcuffing him at the time," Sgobba said. 
</P>
<P>
Sgobba did not identify the injured deputy marshal, saying his wife had not yet 
been notified of the incident. The bailiff, who has been with the marshal's 
office for about a year and half, was taken by ambulance to UC San Diego 
Medical Center, where he was listed in good condition. 
</P>
