<P>
Einstein News Footage Missing: Nearly 4,000 feet of film on Albert Einstein 
that was part of the University of South Carolina's Movietonews collection fell 
out the back door of a Federal Express delivery truck in Columbia, S.C., and 
has been missing for a week. 
</P>
<P>
"From a historical standpoint, it is absolutely irreplaceable," said Don 
McCallister of the university's News Film Library. The film shows Einstein 
appearing at events during the '30s. The university was sending the film to New 
Jersey to be copied for a French film maker. BETH KLEID 
