<P>
Metro; Part B; Page 2; Column 2; Metro Desk 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
131 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
FATAL RUNAWAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Boyle Heights man was killed Tuesday when his big-rig truck rolled over him 
and careened down a steep hill in Boyle Heights. 
</P>
<P>
Zenon J. Duran, 32, had parked the truck on a steep part of City Terrace Drive 
and had placed three bricks against the left front tire as a precautionary 
measure, said California Highway Patrol spokesman Lou Gutierrez. 
</P>
<P>
Just before 8 a.m., the man started his truck and was removing the bricks when 
the truck rolled over him. 
</P>
<P>
The truck cab and its 25-foot trailer rolled for 420 feet down Wabash Street 
before jumping a curb and crashing into an apartment building. Henry Porro, who 
lived in the apartment, was taking his wife to work at the time. 
</P>
<P>
Duran was dead on arrival at County-USC Medical Center. No one else was 
injured, Gutierrez said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
