<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: 8 HOSPITALIZED AS FUMES SHUT DOWN 
COURTHOUSE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Eight employees were hospitalized and the Torrance courthouse closed for more 
than two hours Tuesday after a security guard trying to remove a floor stain 
mistakenly mixed chlorine and ammonia, creating hydrochloric acid fumes that 
filled the five-story building. 
</P>
<P>
The guard was trying to remove stains in a first-floor hallway of the 
courthouse on Maple Avenue at 10:30 a.m. when he poured the two cleaning agents 
into a bucket, said Chris Crawford, administrator of the South Bay Municipal 
Court. 
</P>
<P>
Several employees on the first and second floors soon reported shortness of 
breath and nausea, and the guard and seven others were taken to Little Company 
of Mary Hospital and Torrance Memorial Medical Center. All were later released. 
</P>
</TEXT>
