</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Miami Hurricanes are considering a move from independent status to the 
Atlantic 10 Conference in basketball, which would take effect when Penn State 
joins the Big Ten, a Miami official said. 
</P>
<P>
"We have had some discussions with the Atlantic 10," Miami Associate Athletic 
Director Larry Wahl said. 
</P>
<P>
"That's about where it is right now -- discussions. We're looking at anything 
that makes sense, whether it's an all-sports conference, or whether it will be 
to remain independent in football." 
</P>
<P>
In recent months, West Virginia and other Eastern football independents have 
talked about forming an all-sports conference. Those talks took on greater 
urgency after Penn State announced that it was leaving the Atlantic 10 for the 
Big Ten, a move that will be complete in all sports by the mid-1990s. 
</P>
</TEXT>
