<HEADLINE>
<P>
CHARGER LINEBACKER JOE CAMPBELL IS SIGNED BY RAIDERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CURT HOLBREICH 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Raiders signed Plan B free-agent linebacker Joe Campbell of the San Diego 
Chargers, according to Campbell's agent, Mike Merkow. 
</P>
<P>
Merkow said Campbell signed two one-year contracts with the Raiders. 
</P>
<P>
Campbell, 6 feet 3 1/2 and 242 pounds, was a fourth-round draft choice from New 
Mexico State by the Chargers in 1988. As a rookie he had 15 tackles and three 
sacks but spent six games last season on the inactive list. CURT HOLBREICH 
