<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO SPORTS ET CETERA: CHARGERS LOSE CAMPBELL TO RAIDERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CURT HOLBREICH 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Chargers lost their second player to Plan B free-agency Tuesday when the 
Raiders signed linebacker Joe Campbell, according to Campbell's agent, Mike 
Merkow. 
</P>
<P>
Merkow said Campbell signed two one-year contracts with the Raiders. 
</P>
<P>
Campbell, 6-feet-3 1/2 and 242 pounds, was a fourth-round draft choice out of 
New Mexico State by the Chargers in 1988. As a rookie, he a 15 tackles, three 
sacks and 12 quarterback hits but spent six games this past season on the 
inactive list. 
</P>
<P>
Earlier, the Chargers lost offensive tackle Brett Miller to the New York Jets 
in the Plan B program. CURT HOLBREICH 
