<P>
U.S. Carriers on Time More Often: Major U.S. airlines improved in the number of 
on-time flights and received fewer baggage-handling complaints in January, the 
government reported. 
</P>
<P>
The Transportation Department, in its monthly Air Travel Consumer Report, said 
the largest domestic carriers reported that 77.6% of their flights were on time 
during the month, compared to 70.2% in December. Southwest Airlines had the 
best on-time record for the month, with 82.5%. Eastern had the worst, with 
70.7%. 
