<TEXT>
<P>
Rykoff-Sexton Inc.: Third-quarter profit fell to $610,000 from $4.5 million a 
year ago. 
</P>
<P>
Sales increased 8% to $343.4 million. The Los Angeles company said the results 
reflected lower-than-anticipated sales increases, along with delays in cost 
containment measures. Higher labor, rental, insurance and interest expenses 
also contributed, as well as a non-recurring $2-million pretax charge related 
to bad debt provisions and employee health-care benefits. Rykoff-Sexton Inc. 
manufactures and distributes products to the food service industry. 
