<DATELINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
John Paulsen of Corona del Mar High School scored 30 points to lead the Sea 
Kings to go to a 67-65 upset over second-seeded San Diego Lincoln in the first 
round of the Southern California Division III regional playoffs in San Diego. 
</P>
<P>
Paulsen, a 6-foot-1 senior forward, lifted his team from a six-point deficit at 
the start of the second quarter to an eight-point lead, scoring Corona del 
Mar's first 14 points of the quarter. 
</P>
<P>
Corona del Mar made 16 of 18 free throws, Lincoln made 11 of 21. Jeff Jackson 
added 10 points for Corona del Mar. 
</P>
<P>
Lincoln made a 10-4 run early in the fourth quarter and led, 57-55, with 4:34 
to go. But Corona del Mar scored 10 of the next 14 points to take a 65-61 lead 
with less than a minute remaining. JOHN GEIS 
</P>
