<HEADLINE>
<P>
3 STUDENTS FROM COUNTY WIN MUSIC CENTER SCHOLARSHIPS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By RICK VANDERKNYFF 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
LOS ANGELES 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Three Orange County students on Monday night were among the winners of the 
Spotlight Awards Competition, sponsored by the Music Center of Los Angeles 
County. 
</P>
<P>
Lynette Tapia of San Clemente High School won a $5,000 scholarship in the vocal 
music category, while the Cal State Fullerton team of Chris DuVal and Jeremy 
Johnson each won $3,750 scholarships after tying for first place in the drama 
division. 
</P>
<P>
Jennifer Nunes of Garden Grove High School won a $2,500 scholarship as 
runner-up in the dance category. There were no Orange County finalists in a 
fourth category, instrumental music. 
</P>
<P>
Eleven finalists for the awards competed at the Dorothy Chandler Pavilion for 
$40,000 in scholarship money. They were selected from among 387 applicants. 
</P>
<P>
Tapia, a 16-year-old soprano, sang the "Gavotte" from Massenet's opera "Manon." 
DuVal and Johnson, both 19, performed a scene from William Shakespeare's "The 
Two Gentlemen of Verona."RICK VANDERKNYFF 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, Chris DuVal, left, appears stunned after he and partner Jeremy Johnson 
are presented Spotlight Award for drama on Monday. MINDY SCHAUER / For The 
Times; Photo, Jennifer Nunes, left, was runner-up in dance category; Lynette 
Tapia, right, won $5,000 for taking first place in vocal music. 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
