<HEADLINE>
<P>
LOCAL; 
</P>
<P>
OFFICER ADMITS DRUG SCAM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Los Angeles County Sheriff Sgt. Robert R. Sobel, the central figure in a money 
skimming scandal, pleaded guilty today to a federal conspiracy charge and 
admitted his role in the alleged theft of seized drug money. 
</P>
<P>
Sobel, 45, also pleaded guilty to a single count of filing a false income tax 
return and has agreed to cooperate with government prosecutors. 
</P>
<P>
Nine other veteran narcotics officers have pleaded not guilty to charges that 
they participated in the theft of more than $1.4 million in seized drug cash. 
The wife of one of the deputies was also indicted on charges that she helped 
disguise the stolen money in various bank accounts. She also pleaded not 
guilty. 
</P>
</TEXT>
