<HEADLINE>
<P>
NATION; 
</P>
<P>
POINDEXTER JURY TO HEAR NORTH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
WASHINGTON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Oliver L. North will be the first witness at the Iran-Contra trial of his 
former boss, John M. Poindexter, a federal judge ruled today, rejecting a 
defense motion to bar North from testifying because of alleged perjury. 
</P>
<P>
As jury selection for the trial entered its third day, U.S. District Judge 
Harold Greene revealed that Poindexter's lawyers had filed two sealed motions. 
</P>
<P>
The first, which Greene denied, asked that North not be allowed to testify 
during Poindexter's trial because North allegedly committed perjury during his 
own Iran-Contra trial last year. 
</P>
<P>
The second motion by Poindexter's lawyers seeks to limit North's testimony, and 
Greene said he will hold a hearing on that issue later. 
</P>
<P>
Full details of the motions were not clear because they were filed under seal 
and kept secret. Poindexter's lawyer, Richard Beckler, refused to discuss the 
matters in any detail. 
</P>
</TEXT>
