<P>
SIKHS KILL 19 IN PUNJAB MARKET 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
CHANDIGARH, India 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Sikh extremists exploded a grenade and opened fire in a crowded market today in 
Punjab state, and at least 19 people were killed and 38 wounded, police said. 
</P>
<P>
Press Trust of India, citing unofficial reports, gave a higher death toll, 
saying about 25 people were killed. 
</P>
<P>
Police Chief K. P. S. Gill, who provided the police casualty report, said at 
least 10 gunmen were involved in the attack at 8:15 p.m. in Abohar. 
</P>
<P>
Another police spokesman said the attackers wore masks and arrived on foot. 
"Nobody knows how they escaped," he said. 
</P>
