<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE SIDELINES; 
</P>
<P>
TEEN LEAPS 81 1/2 METERS AT ZAO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
ZAO, Japan 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Andreas Goldberger, a 17-year-old Austrian high school student, soared to the 
day's longest ski jump of 81.5 meters on his first try today to win the 
70-meter normal hill event of the FIS International Zao Jump competition. 
</P>
<P>
Goldberger leaped 73 meters on his second jump, earning 193.9 points to beat 
Japan's Shinichi Tanaka by 6.1 points. 
</P>
<P>
Tanaka collected 187.8 points with jumps of 76.5 meters and 75 meters. 
</P>
<P>
Reiichi Mikata of Japan placed third with jumps of 75 meters and 76 meters for 
186.7 points. 
</P>
