<P>
SUNDAY SILENCE, EASY GOER TO MEET IN $1-MILLION INVITATIONAL AUG. 4 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
ARLINGTON HEIGHTS, Ill. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Sunday Silence and Easy Goer, last year's top two U.S. thoroughbreds, will 
renew the hottest rivalry in horse racing at a $1-million invitational race 
Aug. 4. 
</P>
<P>
Arlington International Racecourse said Tuesday that it will host the 1 
1/4-mile race on dirt that will reunite the two horses who thrilled the fans in 
four exciting races last year which ended 3-1 in favor of Sunday Silence. 
</P>
<P>
Sunday Silence won the Kentucky Derby and Preakness, and, in their last 
meeting, the Breeders' Cup Classic in November. Easy Goer denied the black colt 
the honor of the Triple Crown by capturing the Belmont Stakes by eight lengths. 
</P>
<P>
The invitational is to be held at the track in Chicago's northern suburbs less 
than a month before the Arlington Million, a race on grass that features an 
international field. Sunday Silence trainer Charlie Whittingham has nominated 
his horse for that 1 1/4-mile event as well. 
</P>
